-- Ukraine’s State Railways to Increase Cargo Fees, Kommersant Says
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-11-22T08:46:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-22/ukraine-s-state-railways-to-increase-cargo-fees-kommersant-says.html
Ukrzaliznytsya, Ukraine’s state-
managed railway company, wants to increase cargo tariffs by 12
percent from next year,  Kommersant-Ukraine  newspaper reported,
citing Yuriy Merkulov, head of the company’s commercial
directorate.  The tariff increase will boost revenue by 3.6 billion
hryvnia ($440 million) next year, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
